text.tspan: use this one an put it in your "rocks" layer
to have randomly generated rock sizes.
If you want a specific size, use one of the
Put the vehicles you want in the sub-layer of
Layer3 called "vehicles" so that you see them on top
of every objects. It could also be put on the "other" layer
as vehicles are always spawned on top of every objects
but we want to keep things consistent.
Every map need at least 2 bases and 2 spawnpoints.
The base decoration shows the boundaries of the bases
Put the plants/bushes you want in the sub-layer of
Layer1 called "foliage" to keep things consistent.
Put the crate in the sub-layer of Layer1 called "crates"
If you need to put a crate on top of platform/building,
put the crate in the sub-layer of Layer2 called "crates".
In case you need to place a crate on top of a building,
which itself is on top of another building or platform, you
might then need to create a "crates" sub-layer of Layer3.
Right-click on Layer3, add layer>as sub-layer of current and
enter a name (you can also name it crate3, it doesn't matter)
the electric lines are pathes where every node is a post.
Create more nodes if you want to have more posts.
Important: make sure that the path segments are straight
lines and not curves, else the game will convert it as
a multitude of posts which might lead into a crash.
use this one an put it in your "woods_tree" layer
to have randomly generated tree sizes.
use this one an put it in your "woods_fir" layer
to have randomly generated fir tree sizes.
wall elements are pathes where every node is a seperator.
Create more nodes if you want to have more wall elements.
Important: make sure that the path segments are straight
lines and not curves, else the game will convert it as
a multitude of wall elements which might lead into a crash.
this is a group consisting of a start path (blue) and an end path (red).
The start path is the start of your bridge and the end path the end of the bridge.
It's important that both pathes have the same amount of node,
else the game will crash on map load.
A cliff is another platform where the nodes of the starting and end path
build a deck. The nodes of the end path will be at the same height
than the respective node of the start path. You can add as many nodes as
you needMake sure that both pathes have the same amount of nodes,
A tower is another platform variation. The end path (red) properties have all
the informations required, such as the platform height, the wall height, the
wall material, etc. This example will be an octagonal tower shape, but of
course you can make the shape you want by removing or adding nodes.
Here again, make sure the start (blue) and end (red) pathes have the same
amount of nodes, else the game will crash.
This is the shape of a building, in its properties you can set the height, if the roof is
"flat" or "elevated". Flat roofs are accessible with ladders or if the height of the
building doesn't exceed 2m. On default a roof is elevated for height of max 2m
You can also set the material, which is basically refering to the colors, the side and roof textures,
On the left side of the map, in the material layer, you can see the different building materials.
It should be placed in a "objects" sub-layer.
This is the shape of a roof story, which is basically a low building with a different material,
with e.g. no door/windows, etc. It should be placed on a higher layer than the
building below it. The building below should also have a flat roof to have a roof story on it.
It should be placed in a "objects" sub-layer. Make sure that this sublayer is
To strectch a building, select it and press F2, then you can resize it by moving one of the two "square".
If you want to rotate the building object, select it twice and you should see those arrows on the corners of the object.
Remember to NEVER stretch a building object using those arrows, only the rotation arrows should be used!
This is a road element. Put it in the "alpha_road" layer.
It is a bezier curve. It is important that the
ID contains "navigation", else the AI won't use it as a navigation
If you want the mid roadlines to be drawn, add "dot" in the label field.
This is an "offorad" path. Put it in the offroad layer.
It is similar to a "road" element but isn't drawn on the map and neither in the game world.
Make sure that you have "navigation" in the ID.
